HEADWORD: Ostensibly
<hw>Os*ten"si*bly</hw> <pr>(⟦ocr⟧s*t⟦ecr⟧n"s⟦icr⟧*bl⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>adv.</pos> <def>In an ostensible manner; avowedly; professedly;
apparently.</def> <rj><au>Walsh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Ostensibly</qex>, we were intended to prevent filibustering
into Texas, but really as a menace to Mexico.</q> <rj><qau>U. S.
Grant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

